x=y
(a+b)\tan x
\hbox{if}\quad\frac{\cos x}{\cos y}=\frac{a}{b}\quad\hbox{then}\quad   a\tan x+b\tan y=(a+b)\tan\frac{x+y}{2}\ .
\frac{a}{a+b}=\frac{\cos x}{\cos x+\cos y}\ ,\quad \frac{b}{a+b}=\frac{\cos y}{\cos x+\cos y}\ ,
{\rm LHS}   =(a+b)\frac{\sin x+\sin y}{\cos x+\cos y}   =(a+b)\frac{\sin\frac{x+y}{2}\cos\frac{x-y}{2}}{\cos\frac{x+y}{2}\cos\frac{x-y}{2}}   ={\rm RHS}\ .
